;; with NO end qualifier P582) that are NOT dissolved (no P576) and carry an ISO
;; 3166-1 alpha-3 (P298) + official site (P856). Exact QIDs parsed from the SPARQL
;; JSON (no summarizing model). Dissolved/historical states (Czechoslovakia, USSR,
;; East Germany, Byelorussian SSR, …) are excluded by the membership-end + dissolution
;; filters. The 19 G20 countries already live in gov-units.seed.edn / gov-units.g20.edn
;; and are EXCLUDED here (no duplicate ids). EU is supranational (base seed).
;;
;; :sourcing :authoritative + :maintainer-verified — each QID is the Wikidata entity
;; that canonically bears the country's ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 code. :official-url /
;; :provenance = the state's OWN official portal (P856) where recorded, else the
;; Wikidata entity (ISO3↔QID identity verified either way). Observational mirror
;; (G3/G11): descriptive, neutral, never an official channel, never ranked. Live
;; ingest + publication remain operator/Council steps.

